HEADWORD: Mesotrochal
<hw>Mes"o*tro`chal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Meso-</ets> + Gr. <?/ anything round, a hoop.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having the middle of the body surrounded by
bands of cilia; -- said of the larvae of certain marine
annelids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

